  "local_port": 35250,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you find \"coming soon\" projects on Kickstarter and Indiegogo?",
  "response": "Finding \"coming soon\" projects on crowdfunding platforms like **Kickstarter** and **Indiegogo** can help you stay ahead of the curve, discover innovative ideas early, and potentially support projects right from their inception. Here's a comprehensive guide on how to locate these upcoming campaigns on both platforms:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Utilize Platform-Specific Features**\n\n#### **Kickstarter**\n\n- **Upcoming Projects Section:**\n  - Kickstarter has an **\"Upcoming\"** category where creators can preview projects scheduled to launch soon.\n  - **How to Access:**\n    - Visit [Kickstarter's Discover Page](https://www.kickstarter.com/discover).\n    - Look for filters or categories that include \"Upcoming\" projects. This might require navigating through menus or using the search function with specific keywords.\n\n- **Launch Date Filtering:**\n  - When browsing, use filters to sort projects by their launch dates. This helps identify projects that are imminent.\n\n#### **Indiegogo**\n\n- **Upcoming Campaigns:**\n  - Indiegogo offers an **\"Upcoming\"** section for projects that have been approved but not yet launched.\n  - **How to Access:**\n    - Go to [Indiegogo's Explore Page](https://www.indiegogo.com/explore).\n    - Use the filtering options to select \"Upcoming\" campaigns, which will display projects slated to go live soon.\n\n- **Event-Based Launches:**\n  - Indiegogo sometimes aligns upcoming projects with specific events or themes. Keeping an eye on event announcements can clue you into upcoming campaigns.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Subscribe to Newsletters and Alerts**\n\nBoth platforms offer newsletters that feature new and upcoming projects.\n\n- **Kickstarter:**\n  - **Newsletter Subscription:**\n    - Scroll to the bottom of Kickstarter's homepage and subscribe to their newsletter.\n    - You'll receive updates on new launches and featured projects.\n  \n- **Indiegogo:**\n  - **Email Alerts:**\n    - Sign up for Indiegogo\u2019s email notifications to get information about upcoming campaigns tailored to your interests.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Follow on Social Media**\n\nCrowdfunding platforms actively promote upcoming projects on their social media channels.\n\n- **Kickstarter:**\n  - **Twitter, Facebook, Instagram:**\n    - Follow [Kickstarter's official accounts](https://www.kickstarter.com/about/social) to receive real-time updates on new and upcoming projects.\n  \n- **Indiegogo:**\n  - **Social Platforms:**\n    - Follow [Indiegogo's social media profiles](https://www.indiegogo.com/about#social) for announcements and sneak peeks of upcoming campaigns.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Leverage Third-Party Tools and Websites**\n\nSeveral third-party platforms aggregate information about upcoming crowdfunding projects.\n\n- **Kicktraq:**\n  - **Website:** [Kicktraq.com](https://www.kicktraq.com)\n  - **Features:**\n    - Tracks Kickstarter campaigns, including projections for upcoming projects.\n    - Provides analytics and trends which can help identify promising upcoming projects.\n\n- **BackerKit:**\n  - **Website:** [BackerKit.com](https://www.backerkit.com)\n  - **Features:**\n    - While primarily a post-campaign management tool, BackerKit sometimes features upcoming projects and tools to track them.\n\n- **Indiegogo-Specific Tools:**\n  - Search for tools or websites that specialize in Indiegogo campaigns, as they might offer similar tracking features.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Participate in Community Forums and Groups**\n\nEngaging with communities can provide insider information about upcoming projects.\n\n- **Reddit:**\n  - **Subreddits:**\n    - [r/Kickstarter](https://www.reddit.com/r/kickstarter/)\n    - [r/Indiegogo](https://www.reddit.com/r/Indiegogo/)\n    - Community members often discuss and announce upcoming projects here.\n\n- **Facebook Groups:**\n  - Join groups dedicated to crowdfunding where members share information about new and upcoming campaigns.\n\n- **Discord Servers:**\n  - Some communities have Discord channels where enthusiasts discuss and preview upcoming projects.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Follow Creators and Innovators**\n\nMany creators on these platforms might have multiple projects in the pipeline.\n\n- **Creator Profiles:**\n  - Follow specific creators whose work you admire. They often announce upcoming projects on their profiles before launching them.\n\n- **Personal Websites and Blogs:**\n  - Creators may use their personal platforms to preview upcoming campaigns, providing an early look before they go live on Kickstarter or Indiegogo.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Set Up Google Alerts and RSS Feeds**\n\nStay proactive by setting up alerts for keywords related to upcoming projects.\n\n- **Google Alerts:**\n  - **Setup:**\n    - Go to [Google Alerts](https://www.google.com/alerts).\n    - Create alerts with keywords like \"upcoming Kickstarter project,\" \"new Indiegogo campaign,\" etc.\n    - Receive email notifications when new content matching these terms is published.\n\n- **RSS Feeds:**\n  - If Kickstarter or Indiegogo offer RSS feeds for their upcoming projects, subscribe to them using an RSS reader to get timely updates.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Attend Webinars and Virtual Events**\n\nBoth platforms occasionally host events where upcoming projects are showcased.\n\n- **Kickstarter:**\n  - **Events:**\n    - Look out for Kickstarter-hosted webinars or live streams where creators present their upcoming projects.\n\n- **Indiegogo:**\n  - **Webinars and Workshops:**\n    - Participate in Indiegogo\u2019s educational events to learn about new initiatives and upcoming campaigns.\n\n---\n\n### **9. Monitor Press Releases and News Articles**\n\nMedia outlets often feature stories about innovative upcoming projects.\n\n- **Tech and Innovation Blogs:**\n  - Websites like TechCrunch, Engadget, and Wired regularly cover new crowdfunding campaigns.\n  \n- **Press Release Platforms:**\n  - Keep an eye on platforms like PR Newswire for official announcements about upcoming projects.\n\n---\n\n### **10. Engage Directly with Platforms**\n\nSometimes, directly interacting with the platforms can yield information.\n\n- **Customer Support and Community Managers:**\n  - Reach out to Kickstarter or Indiegogo support teams or community managers to inquire about upcoming projects or newsletter sign-ups.\n\n---\n\nBy combining these strategies, you can effectively discover and stay informed about \"coming soon\" projects on Kickstarter and Indiegogo. Being proactive and engaging with multiple channels increases your chances of uncovering innovative campaigns early, allowing you to support creators and ideas that align with your interests.",
